1
00:00:48,173 --> 00:00:50,300
I said I want us to stay friends.

2
00:00:50,383 --> 00:00:51,968
I said I want to keep seeing you.

3
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:55,805
I let you have your way three years ago,
so it's your turn to do so.

4
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:57,599
You only care about your feelings.

5
00:00:57,682 --> 00:01:00,894
Bad guys always care
only about themselves.

6
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,940
You told me
to take care of myself before others.

7
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:10,487
Whether it's a curse or something else,

8
00:01:11,488 --> 00:01:13,031
I'm ending everything here today.

9
00:01:13,114 --> 00:01:15,075
How?

10
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:17,994
Whether it's a curse, me,
or something else?

11
00:01:41,851 --> 00:01:43,061
The curse

12
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:46,272
is lifted now.

13
00:02:00,703 --> 00:02:01,704
Excuse me.

14
00:02:02,872 --> 00:02:04,290
Excuse me.

15
00:02:04,374 --> 00:02:06,251
Could you put your seat upright?

16
00:02:25,728 --> 00:02:27,021
It really is different.

17
00:03:05,894 --> 00:03:06,769
Gyeong Woo-yeon?

18
00:03:11,858 --> 00:03:13,192
I missed you.

19
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:14,819
You won't be here.

20
00:03:14,903 --> 00:03:16,279
Is it a token of apology?

21
00:03:16,362 --> 00:03:17,697
It's just juice.

22
00:03:24,913 --> 00:03:26,581
It's okay to get lost.

23
00:03:26,664 --> 00:03:28,333
It will tell you where to go.

24
00:03:32,253 --> 00:03:33,588
I must be going insane.

25
00:03:40,261 --> 00:03:41,346
It's hot.

26
00:04:03,326 --> 00:04:05,954
Woo-yeon, want to grab a beer?

27
00:04:06,037 --> 00:04:08,915
WOO-YEON, WANT TO GRAB A BEER?

28
00:04:08,998 --> 00:04:10,208
Sure.

29
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:12,168
I'll call you after dinner.

30
00:04:14,337 --> 00:04:15,964
What did I expect?

31
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:19,801
What? Why was he there?

32
00:04:20,385 --> 00:04:22,762
The owner of the guesthouse
Sang-hyeok told me about

33
00:04:23,346 --> 00:04:24,597
is Su's father's friend.

34
00:04:25,181 --> 00:04:26,683
He met the owner through Su, too.

35
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:30,770
Is that why you made 35 candles?
Because you had a lot on your mind?

36
00:04:30,853 --> 00:04:32,021
No, I didn't.

37
00:04:32,105 --> 00:04:35,733
-I just made them because I wanted to.
-Why did you have a lot on your mind?

38
00:04:36,526 --> 00:04:38,194
Are you falling for him again?

39
00:04:38,278 --> 00:04:40,154
You foolish homo sapiens. You pushover.

40
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:42,240
I'm not falling for him.

41
00:04:44,409 --> 00:04:45,535
Did you sleep with him?

42
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:51,916
Gosh, Yeong-hui.

43
00:04:52,000 --> 00:04:54,627
Come on. Think about
all those nights you spent there

44
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:56,754
and all those morning suns you saw.

45
00:04:57,338 --> 00:04:59,299
-But there's only one sun.
-Anyway,

46
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:01,801
there's no way nothing happened.

47
00:05:01,884 --> 00:05:04,262
You were in the romantic Jeju Island.

48
00:05:06,222 --> 00:05:08,850
What's going on?
Why is your face getting red?

49
00:05:08,933 --> 00:05:10,685
What did you do? Why is it red?

50
00:05:11,269 --> 00:05:12,770
I didn't do anything.

51
00:05:19,610 --> 00:05:20,611
Oh, right.

52
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:23,823
I broke the curse.

53
00:05:23,906 --> 00:05:25,533
How did you break the curse?

54
00:05:26,993 --> 00:05:28,828
I said I won't see him again.

55
00:05:28,911 --> 00:05:31,873
We won't
run into each other again, anyway.

56
00:05:31,956 --> 00:05:34,876
If it was that easy to lift the curse,

57
00:05:34,959 --> 00:05:36,461
it wouldn't have taken ten years.

58
00:05:37,128 --> 00:05:39,922
It's lifted anyway.

59
00:05:41,299 --> 00:05:42,300
But

60
00:05:42,925 --> 00:05:45,762
doesn't a curse get lifted
when the witch is dead?

61
00:06:02,862 --> 00:06:04,655
A girl's earring? What is this?

62
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:21,589
What brings you here?

63
00:06:22,173 --> 00:06:24,592
Su. It's about your mother.

64
00:06:34,435 --> 00:06:36,229
Places contain memories.

65
00:06:41,818 --> 00:06:43,152
To me, Seoul was

66
00:06:44,362 --> 00:06:46,030
a place of nightmares.

67
00:06:46,114 --> 00:06:48,199
Fine! Let's get a divorce!

68
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:57,041
Your mother and I decided to stay friends.

69
00:06:57,125 --> 00:07:00,878
You stayed friends after your divorce.
Don't you care what people might think?

70
00:07:03,172 --> 00:07:04,632
It was a strange world.

71
00:07:06,509 --> 00:07:10,138
You're a breeze.
You just go around everywhere.

72
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:13,015
Then I'll be a flower breeze.
It sounds pretty.

73
00:07:15,726 --> 00:07:17,728
Now that I think of it, it's so mean.

74
00:07:17,812 --> 00:07:20,064
Why does it have to come
and drop all the petals?

75
00:07:20,648 --> 00:07:23,818
It doesn't come to drop petals.
I guess it just comes to see flowers.

76
00:07:24,318 --> 00:07:26,070
Even when I could go anywhere…

77
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:29,157
Visit again later, Woo-yeon.
I had fun with you.

78
00:07:31,200 --> 00:07:33,035
Oh, even if you do, I won't be here.

79
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:35,455
You're not coming back to Seoul?

80
00:07:35,955 --> 00:07:37,874
No. I'm not.

81
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:41,085
I see.

82
00:07:45,256 --> 00:07:47,383
…I never wanted to stay in Seoul.

83
00:07:52,805 --> 00:07:54,807
I was told she was dying.

84
00:07:54,891 --> 00:07:56,601
You even made your friend lie.

85
00:07:57,101 --> 00:07:58,644
I thought she was going to die.

86
00:07:58,728 --> 00:08:00,897
She just sprained her back a bit.

87
00:08:00,980 --> 00:08:03,900
Hey, the spine is a really important
part of the body.

88
00:08:03,983 --> 00:08:05,943
If the core loses balance…

89
00:08:09,238 --> 00:08:11,449
Your mother missed you a lot.

90
00:08:13,034 --> 00:08:16,120
When I missed you guys,
you weren't there for me.

91
00:08:16,662 --> 00:08:17,872
Su.

92
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:19,373
I'm leaving. I'm tired.

93
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:21,584
Wait. Let me drop you off.

94
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:27,215
Don't be nice to me all of a sudden.
It's awkward.

95
00:08:39,227 --> 00:08:42,355
I guess we deeply hurt our boy.

96
00:08:43,981 --> 00:08:46,400
-Min-a, hand me a stapler.
-Okay.

97
00:08:49,612 --> 00:08:51,280
Did you buy all that for yourself?

98
00:08:51,364 --> 00:08:53,199
Yes, for when I'm low on sugar.

99
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:57,161
If you eat stuff like this, it won't be
the problem. It'll be your image.

100
00:08:57,828 --> 00:08:59,789
Take care of yourself
if you want affection.

101
00:09:02,041 --> 00:09:03,417
Ms. Kim. You, too.

102
00:09:03,501 --> 00:09:06,462
Don't get too comfortable
in a long-term relationship.

103
00:09:06,546 --> 00:09:07,713
You must make an effort.

104
00:09:07,797 --> 00:09:10,800
Don't dress casually because
you dated the guy for a long time.

105
00:09:10,883 --> 00:09:13,636
Even if you've dated a long time,
you should make an effort.

106
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:16,097
It's good to have such manners, isn't it?

107
00:09:16,764 --> 00:09:17,765
Yes.

108
00:09:19,141 --> 00:09:20,518
What's that now?

109
00:09:21,894 --> 00:09:25,690
I need to look at some
good things in my life.

110
00:09:25,773 --> 00:09:27,233
As a guy, they don't look hot.

111
00:09:27,900 --> 00:09:29,569
How are they any different from me?

112
00:09:31,862 --> 00:09:33,864
There's a difference between you and them.

113
00:09:34,448 --> 00:09:37,034
I like them
even when they don't do anything.

114
00:09:37,118 --> 00:09:39,120
And I just want you to do nothing.

115
00:09:45,042 --> 00:09:48,337
Ms. Kim, I didn't peg you
to be the funny type.

116
00:09:49,005 --> 00:09:50,214
What a compliment.

117
00:10:08,524 --> 00:10:10,359
I've been wondering for a while…

118
00:10:12,862 --> 00:10:14,697
Is your family rich, by any chance?

119
00:10:17,867 --> 00:10:21,662
I've never
been well-off in my entire life.

120
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:25,791
Then how can you always be so confident?

121
00:10:27,752 --> 00:10:29,962
If I had a lot to lose,
I'd watch out for myself.

122
00:10:30,046 --> 00:10:33,090
But my health and my pride are

123
00:10:33,174 --> 00:10:34,634
the only two things I have.

124
00:10:34,717 --> 00:10:37,386
So I should protect
the only things I have.

125
00:10:38,888 --> 00:10:42,058
And it's not like this job pays enough
to compensate for my pride.

126
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:47,980
So you shouldn't lower
your own self-esteem for other people.

127
00:10:48,898 --> 00:10:52,026
If you do, you have to bow and kneel.

128
00:10:52,109 --> 00:10:54,779
Later, you'll end up like that.

129
00:10:59,075 --> 00:11:00,368
She's so cool.

130
00:11:07,416 --> 00:11:08,501
Hello, Mother.

131
00:11:10,211 --> 00:11:12,671
I see. Father's birthday?

132
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:15,216
I see. At home?

133
00:11:15,299 --> 00:11:19,470
We're going to have a simple dinner
with the family. It's been a while.

134
00:11:19,970 --> 00:11:23,307
Don't buy anything. There's no need to
feel obligated. Come comfortably.

135
00:11:23,391 --> 00:11:26,227
I see. Okay.
By what time should I be there?

136
00:11:27,269 --> 00:11:28,562
One in the afternoon?

137
00:11:30,231 --> 00:11:32,191
But you said it was dinner.

138
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:39,198
I see. Right. To have dinner,
we should prepare it in the afternoon.

139
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:43,160
Okay. I got it. Okay.

140
00:11:47,790 --> 00:11:49,667
So by "comfortably," she meant I should

141
00:11:50,751 --> 00:11:52,336
dress comfortably to do chores.

142
00:13:08,204 --> 00:13:10,498
UNCLE

143
00:13:12,750 --> 00:13:14,543
I don't need a traitor.

144
00:13:15,503 --> 00:13:18,881
Don't call me a traitor. I did it for you.

145
00:13:18,964 --> 00:13:22,468
You seem to want me
to get along with my parents.

146
00:13:22,551 --> 00:13:25,888
I just want you to be happy.

147
00:13:25,971 --> 00:13:27,890
Then you shouldn't have sent me here.

148
00:13:27,973 --> 00:13:30,434
Seoul is nice. It's beautiful.

149
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:33,229
I don't like Seoul. It's boring here.

150
00:13:33,312 --> 00:13:35,773
I don't think that's the word.
You're lonely there.

151
00:13:37,399 --> 00:13:39,818
Emotions are like living organisms.

152
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:43,072
If you cover them up and look
the other way, they grow.

153
00:13:44,073 --> 00:13:45,741
Especially hatred.

154
00:13:46,242 --> 00:13:48,744
It feeds on our memories
and keeps growing.

155
00:13:50,371 --> 00:13:52,248
You can create new memories.

156
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:54,875
Or you can pour it out of your chest.

157
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:57,962
Whatever you do, don't just neglect it.

158
00:14:00,422 --> 00:14:02,758
What? Are you drunk?

159
00:14:07,346 --> 00:14:08,639
Are you in Jeju Island?

160
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:39,420
I would like to order the couples'
passport cases with your calligraphy.

161
00:14:39,503 --> 00:14:43,007
Write, "People who are meant to be
will cross paths."

162
00:14:55,477 --> 00:14:56,896
I'm hungry.

163
00:15:00,941 --> 00:15:04,737
PEOPLE WHO ARE MEANT TO BE
WILL CROSS PATHS

164
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:10,451
Thank you.

165
00:15:16,665 --> 00:15:17,499
Woo-yeon?

166
00:15:21,837 --> 00:15:23,130
Hello.

167
00:15:24,465 --> 00:15:27,009
I have the TV on at my house.

168
00:15:27,092 --> 00:15:31,221
The electricity bill is crazy, especially
with the progressive rate system.

169
00:15:32,056 --> 00:15:33,307
Bye.

170
00:15:41,523 --> 00:15:42,566
Woo-yeon.

171
00:15:50,074 --> 00:15:51,742
Why did you ignore me when I said hi?

172
00:15:52,368 --> 00:15:53,869
You stopped me to hear me say hi?

173
00:15:53,953 --> 00:15:55,412
You just ruined my day.

174
00:15:55,496 --> 00:15:57,539
I was doing fine until you ruined it.

175
00:15:57,623 --> 00:16:00,292
-Why are you ignoring me?
-It's the other way around.

176
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:03,420
I said I didn't want to see you again.

177
00:16:03,504 --> 00:16:05,130
That includes

178
00:16:05,214 --> 00:16:08,258
even when we run into each other
like this. I don't want to say hi.

179
00:16:10,177 --> 00:16:11,595
But I never agreed to it.

180
00:16:13,389 --> 00:16:15,641
And I need to ask you something.

181
00:16:18,519 --> 00:16:20,104
Why did you kiss me that day?

182
00:16:21,313 --> 00:16:22,398
Hey.

183
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:26,026
How can you ask that so bluntly?

184
00:16:26,110 --> 00:16:29,154
Then what should I do?
Will you answer me if I act all shy?

185
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:33,033
Why did you kiss me?

186
00:16:40,332 --> 00:16:43,585
Everything is a joke to you, right?
Nothing's serious to you.

187
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:46,505
-Everything's easy for you.
-I'm not joking. It was a question.

188
00:16:46,588 --> 00:16:47,756
Fine.

189
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,217
I'm sorry about that day.

190
00:16:52,094 --> 00:16:53,053
I apologize.

191
00:16:53,929 --> 00:16:55,723
-What?
-Other people ask if they should

192
00:16:55,806 --> 00:16:58,475
apologize or confess
their feelings after a kiss.

193
00:16:59,852 --> 00:17:01,729
But I won't even ask. I'll apologize.

194
00:17:03,981 --> 00:17:05,232
I'm sorry.

195
00:17:06,984 --> 00:17:08,819
I deserve to die for what I did.

196
00:17:11,196 --> 00:17:12,740
No, you don't deserve to die.

197
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:15,200
You harassed me. It's sexual harassment.

198
00:17:15,284 --> 00:17:19,079
Hey, don't get all legal on me.

199
00:17:19,163 --> 00:17:20,706
You said you deserved to die.

200
00:17:21,290 --> 00:17:23,125
You've committed a crime, now pay for it.

201
00:17:23,208 --> 00:17:25,335
As a punishment,
you have to keep seeing me.

202
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:26,795
And I reject

203
00:17:27,921 --> 00:17:28,881
your rejection.

204
00:17:30,632 --> 00:17:31,633
Hey.

205
00:17:36,680 --> 00:17:37,973
What a jerk.

206
00:17:39,975 --> 00:17:41,810
So the kiss meant nothing to you, right?

207
00:17:46,398 --> 00:17:48,067
You refused another blind date.

208
00:17:49,777 --> 00:17:51,570
Mom is very worried.

209
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:54,615
Blind dates are too uncomfortable.

210
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:59,328
How about this? Why don't you
set him up with one of your friends?

211
00:17:59,411 --> 00:18:00,788
Shall I?

212
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:03,165
What kind of woman does he like?

213
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:05,584
What was your first love like?

214
00:18:10,464 --> 00:18:12,216
-Did you know her?
-What?

215
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:14,343
You've been friends since college.

216
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:17,763
I'm not sure.

217
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:21,767
I prefer to meet naturally.

218
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:25,604
I hope you're still not holding out
for "the one."

219
00:18:27,189 --> 00:18:28,440
I might be.

220
00:18:30,526 --> 00:18:32,611
HAPJEONG-DONG POST OFFICE

221
00:18:40,327 --> 00:18:41,870
SENDER: GYEONG WOO-YEON

222
00:18:42,454 --> 00:18:44,581
-Thank you.
-Thank you. Take care.

223
00:18:48,043 --> 00:18:52,172
I'm the one who ordered the passport
cases. Please cancel my order.

224
00:18:52,256 --> 00:18:53,549
What?

225
00:18:54,133 --> 00:18:56,760
I'm sorry. But custom orders

226
00:18:56,844 --> 00:18:58,971
can't be canceled, exchanged, or refunded

227
00:18:59,054 --> 00:19:01,807
due to a change of heart.
I notified you of this in advance.

228
00:19:05,602 --> 00:19:06,854
We broke up.

229
00:19:06,937 --> 00:19:08,939
WE BROKE UP

230
00:19:14,278 --> 00:19:16,155
Your refund is complete.

231
00:19:16,238 --> 00:19:18,240
So many people canceled this month.

232
00:19:19,449 --> 00:19:21,535
This is why I can't quit my part-time job.

233
00:19:26,039 --> 00:19:26,874
Sir.

234
00:19:28,041 --> 00:19:31,044
Mr. On, the calligrapher
we hired for today's event

235
00:19:31,128 --> 00:19:33,005
broke her wrist.

236
00:19:34,756 --> 00:19:36,425
We have three hours until the event.

237
00:19:36,508 --> 00:19:38,760
Can we hire another calligrapher
in three hours?

238
00:19:38,844 --> 00:19:40,929
We are looking for
a replacement right now.

239
00:19:41,013 --> 00:19:43,223
But we don't have much time left.

240
00:19:43,307 --> 00:19:46,643
For now, prepare a package
with our merchandise for every guest

241
00:19:46,727 --> 00:19:48,520
just in case the event gets canceled.

242
00:19:48,604 --> 00:19:49,938
Yes, sir.

243
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:55,611
-Mr. Min.
-Yes?

244
00:19:56,486 --> 00:19:57,571
Hold on.

245
00:20:02,075 --> 00:20:06,330
HAPJEONG-DONG POST OFFICE

246
00:20:06,413 --> 00:20:09,416
What is it?
Do I need to give another refund?

247
00:20:10,751 --> 00:20:13,462
Hello. This is Min Sang-sik
from Metaphor Publishing House.

248
00:20:13,545 --> 00:20:15,130
I'm contacting you

249
00:20:15,214 --> 00:20:18,050
about a calligraphy event
our company is preparing.

250
00:20:18,133 --> 00:20:19,968
Please call me when you get this.

251
00:20:20,552 --> 00:20:22,054
No freaking way.

252
00:20:24,056 --> 00:20:25,515
PLEASE CALL ME WHEN YOU GET THIS

253
00:20:25,599 --> 00:20:29,645
I don't have her phone number,
so I left a message on her social media.

254
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:31,396
I don't know when she'll check…

255
00:20:31,980 --> 00:20:34,274
"Okay." She said she's coming.

256
00:20:34,900 --> 00:20:37,861
What if this was a scam?
How can she say yes right away?

257
00:20:37,945 --> 00:20:39,404
Because she likes her job.

258
00:20:40,072 --> 00:20:41,114
Do you know her?

259
00:20:41,782 --> 00:20:43,325
I know that she's a calligrapher.

260
00:20:45,786 --> 00:20:49,665
I would very much appreciate it
if you can come to our office.

261
00:20:50,374 --> 00:20:53,794
METAPHOR PUBLISHING HOUSE

262
00:21:03,095 --> 00:21:04,012
This way.

263
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:10,269
Well, I hope it wasn't too troublesome
coming to our office.

264
00:21:10,352 --> 00:21:11,520
-It was fine.
-I see.

265
00:21:11,603 --> 00:21:14,773
I know it was a last-minute request.
But thank you for coming.

266
00:21:14,856 --> 00:21:16,858
No. I should thank you.

267
00:21:19,278 --> 00:21:21,071
He's the CEO of our company.

268
00:21:21,738 --> 00:21:22,823
What?

269
00:21:22,906 --> 00:21:25,575
I told you I like books.

270
00:21:25,659 --> 00:21:28,245
I'm CEO On Jun-su
of Metaphor Publishing House.

271
00:21:28,328 --> 00:21:29,871
I see.

272
00:21:29,955 --> 00:21:32,082
I don't have a business card.

273
00:21:32,165 --> 00:21:34,501
What I got was prettier
than a business card.

274
00:21:34,584 --> 00:21:36,586
-Pardon?
-In the inner pocket of my jacket.

275
00:21:37,337 --> 00:21:39,006
I saw your ID on the postcard.

276
00:21:42,592 --> 00:21:43,844
Please do a good job today.

277
00:21:44,678 --> 00:21:46,763
Okay. I'll do my best.

278
00:21:46,847 --> 00:21:47,973
Let's go.

279
00:21:49,766 --> 00:21:52,728
My marketing team
will explain the details.

280
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:53,812
Okay.

281
00:21:58,775 --> 00:22:01,403
Goodness. It was a lovely painting.

282
00:22:04,614 --> 00:22:07,034
-Anyway, take good care of yourself.
-Thank you.

283
00:22:13,290 --> 00:22:14,666
-Bye.
-Okay.

284
00:22:25,761 --> 00:22:28,680
Why did you call Su? He's busy.

285
00:22:29,473 --> 00:22:32,017
Then why call me? I'm busy, too.

286
00:22:32,100 --> 00:22:33,101
And Dr. Kim as well.

287
00:22:33,894 --> 00:22:36,813
Well, you were the first person
I thought of.

288
00:22:38,690 --> 00:22:40,275
I know you have a lot of time now.

289
00:22:41,693 --> 00:22:43,320
I'm busy, too.

