302
00:23:21,441 --> 00:23:22,984
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

303
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:24,402
MAKE A CALLIGRAPHY WALLPAPER

304
00:23:25,821 --> 00:23:26,905
-Hello.
-Hi.

305
00:23:26,988 --> 00:23:28,406
METAPHOR PUBLISHING HOUSE

306
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:29,533
Say hello.

307
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:32,244
Hello. I'm Lee Yeon-gyeong.

308
00:23:34,830 --> 00:23:39,042
What's the message you wanted to
deliver with your novel?

309
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:42,921
Jae-o is an ordinary guy in his 20s.

310
00:23:43,922 --> 00:23:46,633
He's the guy that we might have
come across once in our lives.

311
00:23:46,716 --> 00:23:49,094
Or perhaps, you could be Jae-o.

312
00:23:50,929 --> 00:23:52,973
In the book, it looks like

313
00:23:53,056 --> 00:23:56,726
Jae-o is walking
through an endless tunnel.

314
00:23:56,810 --> 00:23:59,938
People in their 20s have a hard time
with their jobs and dating lives.

315
00:24:00,021 --> 00:24:01,481
It's natural to mess up.

316
00:24:01,565 --> 00:24:03,358
So there are four tones in Chinese.

317
00:24:03,441 --> 00:24:08,321
First, second, third, and fourth tones.
There's a total of four tones in Chinese.

318
00:24:08,405 --> 00:24:11,533
Depending on how you change your tones,

319
00:24:11,616 --> 00:24:13,910
ma can have different meanings.

320
00:24:13,994 --> 00:24:16,121
Learning the correct intonation
is important.

321
00:24:16,705 --> 00:24:18,582
Shall we begin with the first tone?

322
00:24:19,166 --> 00:24:21,001
Here's the first tone. Ma.

323
00:24:21,084 --> 00:24:22,002
-Ma.
-Ma.

324
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:23,962
-Ma.
-Ma.

325
00:24:24,546 --> 00:24:26,298
This is it for today. Good work.

326
00:24:26,381 --> 00:24:27,883
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

327
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:41,521
Excuse me.
Aren't we going to form study groups?

328
00:24:41,605 --> 00:24:43,899
There are no study groups for Chinese.

329
00:25:14,596 --> 00:25:16,640
LATE-NIGHT FOOD BAR

330
00:25:16,723 --> 00:25:17,557
Here.

331
00:25:18,683 --> 00:25:21,519
Are you still just dating?
Aren't you going to get married?

332
00:25:21,603 --> 00:25:23,521
I do want to get married.

333
00:25:23,605 --> 00:25:27,359
But weddings cost a fortune. I just
finished paying off my student loan.

334
00:25:27,442 --> 00:25:30,028
Don't be like that.
Your boyfriend became a teacher now.

335
00:25:30,111 --> 00:25:32,113
And you have a job with a steady paycheck.

336
00:25:32,197 --> 00:25:36,034
You might not have a lot of money now,
but saving together is all the fun.

337
00:25:36,117 --> 00:25:39,329
We don't have money right now.
We'll end up in debt little by little.

338
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:44,334
-Can you help a girl out here?
-Fat chance of that. I have no money.

339
00:25:47,754 --> 00:25:50,966
See? She doesn't have any money
even at that age.

340
00:25:51,049 --> 00:25:53,176
We'll always be short of money.

341
00:25:53,885 --> 00:25:56,638
If we're always short of money,
when will we get married?

342
00:25:57,472 --> 00:25:58,598
When we have money.

343
00:26:00,642 --> 00:26:04,521
If you accept me,
I'll do my best not to disappoint you.

344
00:26:05,105 --> 00:26:06,690
Leave my boy alone.

345
00:26:08,149 --> 00:26:09,609
That's how you can help me.

346
00:26:09,693 --> 00:26:11,695
I love Gyeong-min, Mother.

347
00:26:11,778 --> 00:26:14,155
-She should check the envelope.
-I'm not your mother.

348
00:26:17,367 --> 00:26:19,452
How much money would you
break up with me for?

349
00:26:24,040 --> 00:26:25,417
Five hundred million won.

350
00:26:26,209 --> 00:26:29,129
So you have a number in mind.
Do you often think about it?

351
00:26:30,005 --> 00:26:33,466
It's too hard to save that much.
I'll be old by then.

352
00:26:38,638 --> 00:26:39,931
I'll give you a billion won.

353
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:41,808
Marry me.

354
00:26:48,315 --> 00:26:49,399
What?

355
00:26:51,693 --> 00:26:54,070
So when will you have one billion won?

356
00:26:59,784 --> 00:27:00,952
When will you have it?

357
00:27:01,995 --> 00:27:03,204
Eat up.

358
00:27:03,288 --> 00:27:04,831
LATE-NIGHT FOOD BAR

359
00:27:04,914 --> 00:27:06,249
Why can't you answer me?

360
00:27:07,375 --> 00:27:08,793
Why are you so quiet?

361
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:11,296
This is what your mother said.

362
00:27:12,005 --> 00:27:14,090
"You're coming
to the birthday party, right?"

363
00:27:14,174 --> 00:27:17,010
She wasn't asking.
It sounded like she was confirming it.

364
00:27:17,761 --> 00:27:20,597
How can I say no when she was
so sure that I would be there?

365
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:23,183
Don't come if you don't want to.

366
00:27:23,266 --> 00:27:25,852
I'm sure she called you
because she wants to see you.

367
00:27:26,686 --> 00:27:29,689
No need to feel pressured.
I won't do anything you don't want.

368
00:27:29,773 --> 00:27:32,275
Your family always ate out
for your father's birthdays.

369
00:27:32,859 --> 00:27:36,237
But she's been cooking meals
ever since I went. Guess what it means.

370
00:27:36,863 --> 00:27:38,114
What does it mean?

371
00:27:38,198 --> 00:27:39,407
"Watch and learn.

372
00:27:39,491 --> 00:27:42,619
This is the family tradition
you must carry on in the future."

373
00:27:44,954 --> 00:27:46,247
Is that what it means?

374
00:27:47,082 --> 00:27:48,917
I made a mistake at the beginning.

375
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,752
I was too young back then.

376
00:27:50,835 --> 00:27:54,589
I didn't know your family would also be
in my life once I met them.

377
00:27:56,424 --> 00:27:58,134
I'm a fool.

378
00:28:00,387 --> 00:28:02,222
-Yeong-hui.
-What?

379
00:28:03,556 --> 00:28:06,393
Stop calling my girl a fool.

380
00:28:06,476 --> 00:28:07,811
Apologize now.

381
00:28:13,149 --> 00:28:15,610
I'm sorry for not doing a better job
in the middle.

382
00:28:15,693 --> 00:28:17,445
I'll talk to my mom.

383
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:21,199
You can just hide behind me.

384
00:28:21,282 --> 00:28:22,450
I'll handle it.

385
00:28:24,285 --> 00:28:26,079
No, don't.

386
00:28:26,162 --> 00:28:29,666
If her precious youngest son does that,
she'll think I put you up to it.

387
00:28:29,749 --> 00:28:33,044
No. My mother is not that old-fashioned.

388
00:28:33,128 --> 00:28:34,295
Are you a mama's boy?

389
00:28:36,673 --> 00:28:37,674
Are you?

390
00:28:38,800 --> 00:28:40,093
Why can't you answer me?

391
00:28:40,885 --> 00:28:42,262
Are you really?

392
00:28:42,762 --> 00:28:45,056
-Hurry up.
-Wait for me.

393
00:28:46,766 --> 00:28:49,811
-Thank you so much for your help today.
-Thank you.

394
00:28:49,894 --> 00:28:51,730
-Please wait.
-Okay.

395
00:28:54,274 --> 00:28:55,275
Mr. On.

396
00:28:58,820 --> 00:29:00,321
Good job today.

397
00:29:00,405 --> 00:29:02,031
I had so much fun today.

398
00:29:03,450 --> 00:29:05,076
Thank you for the opportunity.

399
00:29:05,160 --> 00:29:07,579
Don't thank me for a job
you earned with your skill.

400
00:29:08,913 --> 00:29:11,040
We're going out for a meal. Join us.

401
00:29:11,124 --> 00:29:14,169
No. I don't think I belong there.

402
00:29:14,252 --> 00:29:15,837
No, you do.

403
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:18,757
It's for the people who worked hard
for today's event.

404
00:29:23,636 --> 00:29:26,014
I could open a tteokbokki restaurant
because of you.

405
00:29:26,598 --> 00:29:29,601
You went to a Chinese language school.
Just focus on your studies.

406
00:29:29,684 --> 00:29:32,395
You shouldn't be looking for men to date.
How dare you?

407
00:29:32,479 --> 00:29:35,190
Shut up. You might not know,

408
00:29:35,273 --> 00:29:38,443
but I'm pretty good at Chinese.

409
00:29:38,526 --> 00:29:41,946
What? You can speak Chinese, too.
Who on earth are you?

410
00:29:43,656 --> 00:29:45,325
I should've stuck to a TOEIC school.

411
00:29:45,408 --> 00:29:47,702
Who knew there would be no study groups?

412
00:29:47,786 --> 00:29:50,288
You got a perfect score in TOEIC.
Why would you do that?

413
00:29:50,371 --> 00:29:52,999
If you want to meet guys,
go on blind dates.

414
00:29:53,082 --> 00:29:54,876
I want to meet them organically.

415
00:29:54,959 --> 00:29:59,047
I get the feeling if you insist on meeting
them organically, you might die alone.

416
00:29:59,130 --> 00:30:01,841
But I should probably shut up, right?
I was just about to.

417
00:30:01,925 --> 00:30:03,593
I catch on pretty fast, you know.

418
00:30:06,554 --> 00:30:09,974
Who's coming? Yeong-hui is working late.
And Woo-yeon has other plans.

419
00:30:10,058 --> 00:30:13,061
So you didn't know.
Su said he was going to come over.

420
00:30:15,355 --> 00:30:18,775
My goodness. How long has it been, Su?
Let me see you.

421
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:21,861
You haven't aged at all.
You still look handsome.

422
00:30:21,945 --> 00:30:24,072
No way. I probably look more handsome.

423
00:30:24,155 --> 00:30:25,615
And you're still annoying.

424
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:28,034
Sit right here.
I'll make you a rolled omelet.

425
00:30:30,578 --> 00:30:32,789
Why are you here? How are you here?

426
00:30:32,872 --> 00:30:35,917
-I had to take care of something in Seoul.
-Like what?

427
00:30:37,168 --> 00:30:40,421
-Does Woo-yeon know you're here?
-Yes. We ran into each other yesterday.

428
00:30:41,923 --> 00:30:43,842
I don't want you to see her.

429
00:30:43,925 --> 00:30:46,094
Don't run into her.
Don't even go near her.

430
00:30:46,177 --> 00:30:49,264
-Am I a bomb or something?
-Yes, you are.

431
00:30:49,347 --> 00:30:50,765
A nuclear bomb. A social evil.

432
00:30:51,349 --> 00:30:52,934
Too bad I can't fight a girl.

433
00:30:53,017 --> 00:30:56,229
My gosh. Hey, come on. Let's fight.

434
00:30:56,312 --> 00:30:59,107
Goodness. Hey, I want a beer.

435
00:30:59,190 --> 00:31:00,275
Okay.

436
00:31:05,238 --> 00:31:08,241
All right. If your glasses
are filled, let's raise them.

437
00:31:08,324 --> 00:31:11,786
-Cheers. Good job today.
-Good job.

438
00:31:11,870 --> 00:31:13,454
-Good job.
-Great work.

439
00:31:20,086 --> 00:31:21,379
Who are you, though?

440
00:31:22,046 --> 00:31:23,840
I'm Calligrapher Gyeong Woo-yeon.

441
00:31:24,674 --> 00:31:27,385
My handwriting sucks. I'm always
envious of people like you.

442
00:31:28,887 --> 00:31:32,724
To be honest,
I transcribed a lot of your novels.

443
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:34,767
A creative writing major?

444
00:31:34,851 --> 00:31:38,396
Yes. But I don't write anymore.

445
00:31:38,479 --> 00:31:40,565
It's nice to meet you, Woo-yeon.

446
00:31:40,648 --> 00:31:42,025
Thank you.

447
00:31:45,361 --> 00:31:47,947
-Well done.
-Good job.

448
00:31:54,454 --> 00:31:56,414
Hey, I heard you saw Su yesterday.

449
00:31:56,497 --> 00:32:00,627
He's having a blast
with Jin Sang-hyeok at Tonight.

450
00:32:04,380 --> 00:32:08,176
Oh, my. You can hold your liquor.

451
00:32:08,259 --> 00:32:10,136
You're my kind of girl.

452
00:32:10,637 --> 00:32:12,931
Well, Ms. Lee…

453
00:32:14,098 --> 00:32:16,059
I want your wallet, not your commentary.

454
00:32:21,439 --> 00:32:23,232
-Here.
-Good work, everyone.

455
00:32:23,316 --> 00:32:25,443
-Raise your classes. A ray of sunshine!
-Okay.

456
00:32:25,526 --> 00:32:26,736
A ray of sunshine!

457
00:32:29,697 --> 00:32:31,741
-One more shot?
-Let me pour you a drink.

458
00:32:32,241 --> 00:32:34,160
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

459
00:32:34,243 --> 00:32:35,870
-You're okay, right?
-Yes.

460
00:32:36,663 --> 00:32:37,580
Cheers.

461
00:32:39,707 --> 00:32:42,293
We don't have time to eat the food.

462
00:32:42,794 --> 00:32:45,004
-There's some left. Cheers.
-Cheers.

463
00:32:51,135 --> 00:32:54,013
You guys are truly evil.

464
00:32:54,597 --> 00:32:57,809
I heard you went all the way
to Jeju Island to track down Mr. Han.

465
00:32:57,892 --> 00:33:01,729
You even brought a laptop and forced him
to write after locking him up.

466
00:33:01,813 --> 00:33:04,524
Come on, it was Mr. Han's fault.

467
00:33:04,607 --> 00:33:08,861
And you! Stop pecking at me.

468
00:33:08,945 --> 00:33:11,155
I'll get it done without your nagging.

469
00:33:11,781 --> 00:33:15,034
Do I look like a tree to you?
Are you a woodpecker?

470
00:33:15,118 --> 00:33:17,662
Well, you're not a tree.

471
00:33:18,579 --> 00:33:21,165
Oh, right. My darned CEO once said

472
00:33:21,249 --> 00:33:24,961
writers are the most human-like machines.

473
00:33:25,753 --> 00:33:28,297
What? Machines?

474
00:33:28,381 --> 00:33:30,258
Writers are human, too.

475
00:33:30,842 --> 00:33:33,678
No. I was borrowing what Mr. Han said.

476
00:33:33,761 --> 00:33:36,806
Gosh, but that was your fault.

477
00:33:36,889 --> 00:33:38,599
Why would you say it like that?

478
00:33:39,183 --> 00:33:41,686
Goodness. You're heartless.

479
00:33:43,980 --> 00:33:45,857
You're a tree.

480
00:33:49,527 --> 00:33:52,155
You're a woodpecker.

481
00:33:55,700 --> 00:33:58,369
You're the devil.

482
00:34:02,206 --> 00:34:03,249
Ms. Lee.

483
00:34:04,584 --> 00:34:06,586
You're the devil.

484
00:34:07,795 --> 00:34:10,590
No. That's not it.
Watch. Right where his hair parts.

485
00:34:12,425 --> 00:34:13,718
You're the devil.

486
00:34:15,178 --> 00:34:17,096
Here's your card. Let me do that again.

487
00:34:20,433 --> 00:34:23,019
I should stop here.
I almost got myself in trouble.

488
00:34:23,102 --> 00:34:25,605
-Here you go. Thank you for the card.
-Thank you.

489
00:34:25,688 --> 00:34:28,399
-Thank you.
-Gosh, don't thank me. I didn't do much.

490
00:34:28,483 --> 00:34:30,151
Thank you.

491
00:34:33,571 --> 00:34:36,699
Who knew there would be
no study groups at the Chinese school?

492
00:34:37,450 --> 00:34:40,745
So what? Because there are
so many people in China, they don't date?

493
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:42,163
Why not?

494
00:34:42,246 --> 00:34:44,457
I can smell alcohol from this photo.

495
00:34:45,124 --> 00:34:48,294
No wonder why she and Woo-yeon
are friends. It's crystal clear.

496
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:50,713
Goodness.

497
00:34:53,257 --> 00:34:54,425
What?

498
00:34:56,135 --> 00:34:58,679
You jerk. Get out of Seoul!

499
00:34:58,763 --> 00:35:00,640
Hey, stop telling him to leave Seoul.

500
00:35:00,723 --> 00:35:02,975
He just got here.

501
00:35:03,601 --> 00:35:07,480
Here's why. He's evil.

502
00:35:07,563 --> 00:35:09,023
"Evil"?

503
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:11,859
My gosh, you're totally wasted.

504
00:35:12,443 --> 00:35:14,195
-Bye.
-What? Already?

505
00:35:14,278 --> 00:35:16,489
I should get going. See you.

506
00:35:17,532 --> 00:35:20,660
Bye. Get lost!

507
00:35:25,998 --> 00:35:28,167
"I should get going. See you."

508
00:35:30,920 --> 00:35:31,879
He's cool.

